The Golden Coast National Nature Reserve lies along the coast of the Bohai Bay in north China's Hebei Province. The largest expanse of coastal sand dunes in China formed of a chain of sandy hills, this sand dune system winds southwards. Viewed from the air, it resembles a golden jewel on the Bohai Bay. Check out the video to learn more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Hebei series Hebei Province hosts the largest forest park in northern China, Saihanba National Forest Park, and the country's largest expanse of coastal sand dunes, the Golden Coast National Nature Reserve. Here, you will find unique landforms and a rich variety of plants and animals. For more: Hebei series | Episode 1: Beautiful Highland Hebei series | Episode 2: Boundary River Hebei series | Episode 3: Wetland in the Snow Hebei series | Episode 4: The Rhythm of Winter (Cover image via a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)